A slight Ode, but singular-ly beautiful in expression: it is in Horace's best style, and is apparently perfectly simple because perfectly finished ; summa ars celavit artem. Any one who disagrees should attempt to omit or alter a single word. It is translated by Milton (Occasional Poems).
